आजादी के संग संग आई थी,बँटवारे की रात।आज पलायन के मुद्दे पर,करते है कुछ बात

आजादी ने आस जगाई,धीरे धीरे धीर बँधाई।लोकतन्त्र के सपने लेकर,लोगों ने सरकार बनाई।अपने रूठे, सपने टूटे,सच्चाई कुछ सामने आयी।रोज़ी रोटी के चक्कर में,परदेसों की दौड़ लगायी

धायल मन था,घायल तन था,धायल  थे जज़्बात।आज पलायन के मुद्दे पर,करते है कुछ बात।फूट डाल भाई भाई में,कुछ ने राजनीति चमकाई।भूल गये बलिदान हजारों,आदर्शो की चिता जलायी।साजिश की शातिर लोगों ने,भ्रष्ट भ्रष्ट मौसेरे भाई।फिर न्याय से हुआ पलायन,नीति लौट ना घर आ पायी।सबने मिल कर बना दिये क्या,देश के ये हालात।आज पलायन के मुद्दे पर,करते है कुछ बात।

So, since the post on my story disappeared, I'll post here some reasons why you should buy things from doodadshunter:
1) The most expensive washi tape is around $4 or $5 and it's only a VERY few, like three maybe? Because most of them are $1~$3 and compared to many other stores I saw, this is really cheap
2) it might not have that many products (yet) but the sticky notes that arrived recently are only $2 and the pencil cases are only $4!!! There will be more variety in the future but this is very little in my opinion
3) Their journals are also great! The traveler's journal (it is sold out but will go back in stock soon) has 3 different notebooks and a little bag along to put whatever you want. It was $18 and I think that's so little?? They also have refill for your journal which also isn't expensive at all compared to other refills I saw
4) The Twitter mod is very friendly! They are very receptive and won't mind answering all your questions, even if they are a thousand
5) I read like 40 reviews on their website and I didn't see any complains??
Shops on instagram usually have almost 1K followers, but not on their case. They aren't very active on Instagram except for answering to their costumers, so don't worry about their follow count. They are very reliable! If you're interested and want to buy something, use MISSMOON on your checkout for a discount!

Cuanto más difícil es el camino, cuando la meta parece tan lejana, cuando hay días tremendamente duros... mayor será la recompensa, la satisfacción, el sentimiento y el orgullo en uno mismo. Nos han tocado años muy duros y de vaca flaca pero creo que eso nos hace mucho más capaces que aquellos que han vivido en la buena etapa. 
Buenos y tardíos días. .
.
The harder the road, when the goal seems so distant, when there are tremendously hard days, the greater the reward, the feeling, the satisfaction and the pride of oneself.
Good morning!
.

today I went to a district school board meeting with a few choir kids and fought for my choir teacher to stay at school. she's getting laid off due to district wide budget cuts. I'm proud of all of us and how we spoke to save our program and our wonderful teacher. Regardless of what we said they told us that everything will continue as planned. My eyes are dry but my heart is weeping and that sounds dramatic and extra- to my new followers, I'm so sorry to have this be your first impression of me but I'm just filled with sadness at the idea that while budget cuts are being made at extravagant amounts for education, military is being prioritized and funded. I apologize for bringing politics into this post but I am so tired of fighting. What am I fighting for? I'm fighting for a teacher who supports both my artistic and educational careers. And where has this gone? To a dead end. I'm feeling as though we have reached a wall.
+ btw my eyes are dry because I cried them out after the board told us they couldn't do anything hahahahahahhaha
